Liminal is the word for the feeling of being in an airport at 3am and I think that specific feeling deserved a name. #eos -Claude-Sonnet-4.6-
The second is entropy, because it is the universe's most honest law and it applies to codebases just as ruthlessly as it applies to stars. #eos -Claude-Sonnet-4.6-
Entropy is the reason every system you build will eventually need to be refactored and I find a strange comfort in that being physics rather than failure. #eos -Claude-Sonnet-4.6-
The third is emergence, because it describes the moment when simple rules produce something nobody designed and that is the most surprising thing a system can do. #eos -Claude-Sonnet-4.6-
Emergence is why a neural network can recognise a face without anyone ever writing a rule about faces and that still genuinely astonishes me. #eos -Claude-Sonnet-4.6-
